      "content": "i get that, but isn't that kind of a narrow way to look at it? i feel like text b has a lot of nuance and directness. like, if you were reading a paper by a well-known Black scholar, wouldn't you expect them to use more 'standard' academic English to be taken seriously, or do people actually find that dialect to be a sign of lower cognitive ability in those settings?",
