      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, and i appreciate the nuance. but lets be real for a second—even if the 'intellectual rigor' part is just a preference, in practice doesn't it create a huge gap? \n\nlike, if you were an admissions officer or a hiring manager, and you saw a brilliant candidate who wrote or spoke more like Text B, wouldn't you subconsciously or even consciously assume they might not be as \"educated\" or \"professional\" compared to someone using Text A? isn't there basically a direct link in how people judge a person's intelligence based on these linguistic markers?",
